"title": "4275: Sodom and Gomorrah",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4275",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Two neighbouring cities, probably located at the eastern or south-eastern end of the Dead Sea, noted for their sinfulness. God's response in wrath and judgment serves as a warning to subsequent generations.</p>\n<h2>Sodom and Gomorrah's location</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen10:19\">GEN 10:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:10-Gen13:12\">GEN 13:10–13:12</a></p>\n<h2>Sodom became Lot's home</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:10-Gen13:12\">GEN 13:10–13:12</a></p>\n<h2>Sodom and Gomorrah at war</h2>\n<h3>Sodom and Gomorrah, with other cities of the plain, defeated by the alliance of four kings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:1-Gen14:12\">GEN 14:1–14:12</a></p>\n<h3>Abram rescues Lot and is honoured by the king of Sodom and his allies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:13-Gen14:24\">GEN 14:13–14:24</a></p>\n<h2>The wickedness of Sodom and Gomorrah</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:13\">GEN 13:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:20-Gen18:21\">GEN 18:20–18:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:1-Gen19:9\">GEN 19:1–19:9</a></p>\n<h2>Abraham pleads for the righteous in Sodom and Gomorrah</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:16-Gen18:32\">GEN 18:16–18:32</a></p>\n<h2>God's judgment against Sodom and Gomorrah</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:13\">GEN 19:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:23-Gen19:29\">GEN 19:23–19:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:23\">DEU 29:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:29\">LUK 17:29</a></p>\n<h2>The story of Sodom and Gomorrah becomes a picture of human sinfulness and divine judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:7\">JUD 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:9\">ISA 3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:19\">ISA 13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:14\">JER 23:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:6\">LAM 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:44-Ezek16:58\">EZK 16:44–16:58</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:11\">AMO 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:15\">MAT 10:15</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:12\">LUK 10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:23-Matt11:24\">MAT 11:23–11:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:28-Luke17:30\">LUK 17:28–17:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:6-2Pet2:9\">2PE 2:6–2:9</a></p>",
